.SH "NAME"
we\-blog\-init \- creates or recovers a We\-Blog repository
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
\&\fBwe-blog-init\fR [\fB\-fqV\fR] [\fB\-b\fR \fIdirectory\fR]
.PP
\&\fBwe-blog-init\fR \fB\-h\fR|\fB\-v\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\fBwe-blog-init\fR either creates a fresh new We-Blog repository, or
recovers an existing one in case it is corrupted. Optionally, it can also
revert a configuration and default templates to their original state,
leaving all user data (that is, both blog posts and pages) intact.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
.IP "\fB\-b\fR \fIdirectory\fR, \fB\-\-blogdir\fR \fIdirectory\fR" 4
.IX Item "-b directory, --blogdir directory"
Allows you to specify a \fIdirectory\fR in which the We-Blog repository
is to be placed. The default option is a current working directory.
.IP "\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-force\fR" 4
.IX Item "-f, --force"
Reverts existing configuration, theme, and language files to their initial
state. By default, these files are kept intact.
.IP "\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR" 4
.IX Item "-q, --quiet"
Disables displaying of unnecessary messages.
.IP "\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR" 4
.IX Item "-V, --verbose"
Enables displaying of all messages, including a list of created files.
.IP "\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR" 4
.IX Item "-h, --help"
Displays usage information and exits.
.IP "\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR" 4
.IX Item "-v, --version"
Displays version information and exits.
.SH "EXAMPLE USAGE"
.IX Header "EXAMPLE USAGE"
Create a new blog in a current directory:
.PP
.Vb 2
\&        $ we\-blog\-init
\&        Created a We\-Blog repository in .we\-blog.
.Ve
.PP
Create a new blog in ~/public_html:
.PP
.Vb 2
\&        $ we\-blog\-init \-b ~/public_html
\&        Created a We\-Blog repository in /home/joe/public_html/.we\-blog.
.Ve
.PP
Revert a configuration file and default templates to their initial state:
.PP
.Vb 2
\&        $ we\-blog\-init \-f
\&        Recovered a We\-Blog repository in .we\-blog.
.Ve
.PP
Or if you want to see what files have been reverted:
.PP
.Vb 6
\&        $ we\-blog\-init \-fV
\&        Created .we\-blog/config
\&        Created .we\-blog/theme/default.html
\&        Created .we\-blog/style/default.css
\&        Created .we\-blog/lang/en_US
\&        Recovered a We\-Blog repository in .we\-blog.
.Ve
